The schema migration can leave projection-terminal gaps for dropped edge rows that were pending projection, which can permanently block projection cursor advancement after upgrade. The rest of the inspected changes compile and the engine test suite passed locally, but this migration edge case is a correctness issue.

Review comment:

- [P1] Mark dropped pending edges terminal during migration — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:715-716
  When upgrading a v22 database that has a body-bearing edge whose vector projection has not completed yet, that edge can have no `_fathomdb_projection_terminal` row. This migration deletes/drops all `canonical_edges` rows but only reserves the high-water cursor; `advance_projection_cursor()` still advances one cursor at a time only when a terminal row exists, so the first dropped pending edge becomes a permanent gap and later writes/projections can no longer advance the projection cursor, causing `wait_for_idle`/search freshness checks to stall on upgraded databases.
